Share this on WhatsAppThe daughter of President Muhammadu Buhari, Fatima, on Sunday wedded the former Managing Director of the Federal Mortgage Bank of Nigeria, Malam Gimba Yau Kumo, in Daura, Katsina State.
It was gathered that the invitation cards for the wedding were sent out online last week.
The marriage was solemnized after the traditional prayer at the president’s residence at Mai Aduwa GRA Daura, Katsina State.
Hajiya Fatima Buhari, 38 years, second daughter of the President, was born by Buhari’s first wife, Safinatu, who died few years after their divorce in 1988.
It was gathered that a dinner in honour of the couple will hold in Abuja on Monday.
